=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Guides_Multichannel-Expansion_ex7 ===

DESCRIPTION: A neutral pure_tone sound, with square_like oscillator character around 407 Hz, featuring punchy attack and percussive envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, and filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: neutral
  crest_factor_db: percussive
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: moderate
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 406.9919
  harmonic_decay_rate: -13.4377
  harmonic_regularity: 0.8359
  pitch_clarity: 27.8107
  inharmonicity: 0.7150
  type: square_like
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -24.9478
  resonance_freq: 236.8652

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Multichannel Expansion Example 7
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Guides/Multichannel-Expansion.html
// Tags: Multichannel-Expansion, Guides
